          </summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            No. Everything runs in your browser using JavaScript and the File API. You can verify by opening your browser's DevTools → Network tab and dropping a file — you'll see zero requests. The tool works offline once the page has loaded.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 p-5">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            What image formats are supported?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            JPEG (.jpg, .jpeg), PNG (.png), and WebP (.webp). HEIC (iPhone default) and TIFF are not yet supported — if you drop one, the tool will tell you. The easiest workaround for HEIC is to convert to JPEG on your phone first, or change your iPhone's camera setting to "Most Compatible."
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 p-5">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Does stripping EXIF reduce image quality?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            No. This tool removes only the metadata segments — pixel data is not re-encoded. The output is visually identical to the original. File size drops by whatever metadata weighed (usually 10–200 KB; sometimes more if there was an embedded thumbnail).
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 p-5">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Is the color profile preserved?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. The ICC color profile stays embedded because removing it can shift how colors render on wide-gamut displays. Only personal metadata (GPS, camera, timestamps, text comments) is stripped.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 p-5">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Can I process many photos at once?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. Drop multiple files and each is cleaned independently. There's no file-count cap — memory use is roughly 2× the size of whatever's queued, so ~1 GB of photos is fine on a typical laptop.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Source/trust -->
    <section class="mb-8 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-3">Verify it yourself</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Trust shouldn't be a marketing claim. The entire implementation — JPEG, PNG, and WebP parsers — is open-source and auditable.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/burakoskay/SystemReport/blob/main/src/pages/tools/exif-stripper.astro" rel="noopener" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">
        View source on GitHub
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 6H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 003 8.25v10.5A2.25 2.25 0 005.25 21h10.5A2.25 2.25 0 0018 18.75V10.5m-10.5 6L21 3m0 0h-5.25M21 3v5.25"/></svg>
      </a>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<script>
// --- Format detection ---------------------------------------------------

function detectFormat(buf: Uint8Array): 'jpeg' | 'png' | 'webp' | 'unknown' {
  if (buf.length < 12) return 'unknown';
  if (buf[0] === 0xff && buf[1] === 0xd8) return 'jpeg';
  if (buf[0] === 0x89 && buf[1] === 0x50 && buf[2] === 0x4e && buf[3] === 0x47) return 'png';
  if (
    buf[0] === 0x52 && buf[1] === 0x49 && buf[2] === 0x46 && buf[3] === 0x46 &&
    buf[8] === 0x57 && buf[9] === 0x45 && buf[10] === 0x42 && buf[11] === 0x50
  ) return 'webp';
  return 'unknown';
}

function concatBytes(chunks: Uint8Array[]): Uint8Array {
  let total = 0;
  for (const c of chunks) total += c.length;
  const out = new Uint8Array(total);
  let off = 0;
  for (const c of chunks) { out.set(c, off); off += c.length; }
  return out;
}

// --- JPEG ---------------------------------------------------------------
// Walk JPEG segments. Drop APPn (0xFFE0–0xFFEF) and COM (0xFFFE). Keep
// everything else — DQT, DHT, SOF, SOS + compressed scan data, EOI.
function stripJpeg(buf: Uint8Array): { bytes: Uint8Array; removed: string[] } {
  if (buf[0] !== 0xff || buf[1] !== 0xd8) throw new Error('Not a valid JPEG');
  const keep: Uint8Array[] = [buf.subarray(0, 2)];
  const removed: string[] = [];
  let i = 2;
  while (i < buf.length) {
    if (buf[i] !== 0xff) throw new Error('Malformed JPEG at offset ' + i);
    // Skip fill bytes (0xFF padding between segments).
    let marker = buf[i + 1];
    let p = i + 1;
    while (marker === 0xff && p + 1 < buf.length) { marker = buf[++p]; }
    const markerStart = p - 1;
    if (marker === 0xda) {
      // SOS — rest of the file is compressed scan data + EOI.
      keep.push(buf.subarray(markerStart));
      break;
    }
    if (marker === 0xd9) { // EOI without SOS (weird but handle it)
      keep.push(new Uint8Array([0xff, 0xd9]));
      break;
    }
    const segLen = (buf[markerStart + 2] << 8) | buf[markerStart + 3];
    const segEnd = markerStart + 2 + segLen;
    const isAppN = marker >= 0xe0 && marker <= 0xef;
    const isComment = marker === 0xfe;
    if (isAppN) {
      // Identify the payload — APP1 with "Exif" prefix is EXIF, APP1 "http://ns.adobe.com/xap" is XMP, APP13 is IPTC.
      const sig = String.fromCharCode(
        buf[markerStart + 4] || 0, buf[markerStart + 5] || 0,
        buf[markerStart + 6] || 0, buf[markerStart + 7] || 0,
      );
      if (marker === 0xe1 && sig.startsWith('Exif')) removed.push('EXIF');
      else if (marker === 0xe1) removed.push('XMP');
      else if (marker === 0xed) removed.push('IPTC');
      else if (marker === 0xe2) removed.push('ICC (will re-add)');
      else removed.push(`APP${marker - 0xe0}`);
    } else if (isComment) {
      removed.push('Comment');
    } else {
      keep.push(buf.subarray(markerStart, segEnd));
    }
    i = segEnd;
  }
  return { bytes: concatBytes(keep), removed };
}

// --- PNG ----------------------------------------------------------------
// Walk chunks. Drop tEXt, iTXt, zTXt, eXIf, tIME. Keep IHDR, IDAT, IEND,
// PLTE, tRNS, iCCP (color profile), sRGB, gAMA, cHRM, pHYs, bKGD, sBIT.
function stripPng(buf: Uint8Array): { bytes: Uint8Array; removed: string[] } {
  const sig = [0x89, 0x50, 0x4e, 0x47, 0x0d, 0x0a, 0x1a, 0x0a];
  for (let i = 0; i < 8; i++) if (buf[i] !== sig[i]) throw new Error('Not a valid PNG');
  const stripTypes = new Set(['tEXt', 'iTXt', 'zTXt', 'eXIf', 'tIME']);
  const keep: Uint8Array[] = [buf.subarray(0, 8)];
  const removed: string[] = [];
  let i = 8;
  while (i < buf.length) {
    const len =
      (buf[i] << 24 >>> 0) | (buf[i + 1] << 16) | (buf[i + 2] << 8) | buf[i + 3];
    const type = String.fromCharCode(buf[i + 4], buf[i + 5], buf[i + 6], buf[i + 7]);
    const chunkEnd = i + 8 + len + 4; // length + type + data + CRC
    if (stripTypes.has(type)) {
      removed.push(type);
    } else {
      keep.push(buf.subarray(i, chunkEnd));
    }
    if (type === 'IEND') break;
    i = chunkEnd;
  }
  return { bytes: concatBytes(keep), removed };
}

// --- WebP ---------------------------------------------------------------
// RIFF container. Drop EXIF and XMP chunks. Clear the EXIF/XMP flag bits
// in VP8X so readers don't look for chunks we removed.
function stripWebp(buf: Uint8Array): { bytes: Uint8Array; removed: string[] } {
  const kept: Uint8Array[] = [];
  const removed: string[] = [];
  let i = 12;
  while (i + 8 <= buf.length) {
    const type = String.fromCharCode(buf[i], buf[i + 1], buf[i + 2], buf[i + 3]);
    const size =
      (buf[i + 4]) | (buf[i + 5] << 8) | (buf[i + 6] << 16) | (buf[i + 7] << 24);
    const padded = size + (size & 1);
    const chunkEnd = i + 8 + padded;
    if (type === 'EXIF' || type === 'XMP ') {
      removed.push(type.trim());
    } else {
      let chunk = buf.subarray(i, chunkEnd);
      if (type === 'VP8X') {
        chunk = new Uint8Array(chunk);
        // Clear bit 3 (EXIF) and bit 2 (XMP) in the VP8X flags byte at offset 8.
        chunk[8] &= ~0b00001100;
      }
      kept.push(chunk);
    }
    i = chunkEnd;
  }
  const payloadBytes = kept.reduce((n, c) => n + c.length, 0);
  const riffSize = 4 + payloadBytes; // "WEBP" + payload
  const header = new Uint8Array(12);
  header.set([0x52, 0x49, 0x46, 0x46], 0); // RIFF
  header[4] = riffSize & 0xff;
  header[5] = (riffSize >>> 8) & 0xff;
  header[6] = (riffSize >>> 16) & 0xff;
  header[7] = (riffSize >>> 24) & 0xff;
  header.set([0x57, 0x45, 0x42, 0x50], 8); // WEBP
  return { bytes: concatBytes([header, ...kept]), removed };
}

// --- Orchestrator -------------------------------------------------------

interface Processed {
  name: string;
  origSize: number;
  cleanSize: number;
  cleanedBlob: Blob;
  cleanedUrl: string;
  removed: string[];
  format: string;
  error?: string;
}

async function processFile(file: File): Promise<Processed> {
  const buf = new Uint8Array(await file.arrayBuffer());
  const format = detectFormat(buf);
  try {
    let out: { bytes: Uint8Array; removed: string[] };
    let mime = file.type;
    if (format === 'jpeg') { out = stripJpeg(buf); mime = 'image/jpeg'; }
    else if (format === 'png') { out = stripPng(buf); mime = 'image/png'; }
    else if (format === 'webp') { out = stripWebp(buf); mime = 'image/webp'; }
    else throw new Error('Unsupported format. This tool supports JPEG, PNG, and WebP.');
    const blob = new Blob([out.bytes], { type: mime });
    return {
      name: file.name,
      origSize: buf.length,
      cleanSize: out.bytes.length,
      cleanedBlob: blob,
      cleanedUrl: URL.createObjectURL(blob),
      removed: out.removed,
      format,
    };
  } catch (e: any) {
    return {
      name: file.name,
      origSize: buf.length,
      cleanSize: 0,
      cleanedBlob: new Blob(),
      cleanedUrl: '',
      removed: [],
      format,
      error: e.message,
    };
  }
}

// --- UI -----------------------------------------------------------------

const dropzone = document.getElementById('dropzone')!;
const fileInput = document.getElementById('file-input') as HTMLInputElement;
const results = document.getElementById('results')!;
const bulkActions = document.getElementById('bulk-actions')!;
const downloadAll = document.getElementById('download-all')!;
const clearAll = document.getElementById('clear-all')!;
const processed: Processed[] = [];

function fmtBytes(n: number): string {
  if (n < 1024) return n + ' B';
  if (n < 1024 * 1024) return (n / 1024).toFixed(1) + ' KB';
  return (n / (1024 * 1024)).toFixed(2) + ' MB';
}

function renderRow(p: Processed): HTMLElement {
  const row = document.createElement('div');
  row.className = 'flex items-start gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950';
  if (p.error) {
    row.innerHTML = `
      <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/40 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 dark:text-red-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m9-.75a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0zm-9 3.75h.008v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 truncate">${escapeHtml(p.name)}</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-red-600 dark:text-red-400 mt-0.5">${escapeHtml(p.error)}</p>
      </div>
    `;
    return row;
  }
  const delta = p.origSize - p.cleanSize;
  const removedText = p.removed.length ? p.removed.join(', ') : 'No metadata found — file already clean';
  row.innerHTML = `
    <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/40 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
      <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-600 dark:text-green-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
    </div>
    <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3">
        <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 truncate">${escapeHtml(p.name)}</p>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500 flex-shrink-0 uppercase">${p.format}</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-0.5">
        ${fmtBytes(p.origSize)} → ${fmtBytes(p.cleanSize)}
        ${delta > 0 ? `<span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">(−${fmtBytes(delta)} metadata removed)</span>` : ''}
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Stripped: ${escapeHtml(removedText)}</p>
    </div>
    <a href="${p.cleanedUrl}" download="${escapeHtml(cleanedFilename(p.name))}"
       class="flex-shrink-0 inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 bg-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-100 text-white dark:text-gray-900 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-gray-800 dark:hover:bg-gray-200 transition-colors">
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 16.5v2.25A2.25 2.25 0 005.25 21h13.5A2.25 2.25 0 0021 18.75V16.5M16.5 12L12 16.5m0 0L7.5 12m4.5 4.5V3"/></svg>
      Download
    </a>
  `;
  return row;
}

function escapeHtml(s: string): string {
  return s.replace(/[&<>"']/g, (c) => ({ '&': '&amp;', '<': '&lt;', '>': '&gt;', '"': '&quot;', "'": '&#39;' }[c]!));
}

function cleanedFilename(name: string): string {
  const dot = name.lastIndexOf('.');
  if (dot === -1) return name + '-clean';
  return name.slice(0, dot) + '-clean' + name.slice(dot);
}

async function handleFiles(files: FileList | File[]) {
  const list = Array.from(files);
  if (!list.length) return;
  results.classList.remove('hidden');
  bulkActions.classList.remove('hidden');
  for (const file of list) {
    const placeholder = document.createElement('div');
    placeholder.className = 'flex items-center gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950';
    placeholder.innerHTML = `
      <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 animate-spin" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M16.023 9.348h4.992v-.001M2.985 19.644v-4.992m0 0h4.992m-4.993 0l3.181 3.183a8.25 8.25 0 0013.803-3.7M4.031 9.865a8.25 8.25 0 0113.803-3.7l3.181 3.182m0-4.991v4.99"/></svg>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Processing ${escapeHtml(file.name)}…</p>
    `;
    results.appendChild(placeholder);
    const p = await processFile(file);
    processed.push(p);
    const row = renderRow(p);
    results.replaceChild(row, placeholder);
  }
}

dropzone.addEventListener('click', () => fileInput.click());
dropzone.addEventListener('keydown', (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
  if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') { e.preventDefault(); fileInput.click(); }
});
fileInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
  if (fileInput.files) handleFiles(fileInput.files);
  fileInput.value = '';
});

['dragenter', 'dragover'].forEach((evt) => {
  dropzone.addEventListener(evt, (e: Event) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    dropzone.classList.add('border-gray-900', 'dark:border-gray-100', 'bg-gray-50', 'dark:bg-gray-900/50');
  });
});
['dragleave', 'drop'].forEach((evt) => {
  dropzone.addEventListener(evt, (e: Event) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    dropzone.classList.remove('border-gray-900', 'dark:border-gray-100', 'bg-gray-50', 'dark:bg-gray-900/50');
  });
});
dropzone.addEventListener('drop', (e: DragEvent) => {
  if (e.dataTransfer?.files?.length) handleFiles(e.dataTransfer.files);
});

downloadAll.addEventListener('click', () => {
  for (const p of processed) {
    if (p.error || !p.cleanedUrl) continue;
    const a = document.createElement('a');
    a.href = p.cleanedUrl;
    a.download = cleanedFilename(p.name);
    a.click();
  }
});

clearAll.addEventListener('click', () => {
  for (const p of processed) if (p.cleanedUrl) URL.revokeObjectURL(p.cleanedUrl);
  processed.length = 0;
  results.innerHTML = '';
  results.classList.add('hidden');
  bulkActions.classList.add('hidden');
});
</script>
